  "name": "Life Transference Arrow",
  "desc": "You create a glowing arrow of necrotic magic and command it to strike a creature you can see within range. The arrow can have one of two effects; you choose which at the moment of casting. If you make a successful ranged spell attack, you and the target experience the desired effect. If the attack misses, the spell fails.\n* The arrow deals 2d6 necrotic damage to the target, and you heal the same amount of hit points.\n* You take 2d6 necrotic damage, and the target heals the same amount of hit points.\n",
